{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EahNkUn47oYJ2c61bo6W5D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both verification criteria are satisfied:\n\n1. **Prometheus has 3 active targets** for CockroachDB — one per node, all `health=up`, scraping `https://<pod-ip>:8080/_status/vars` via the `crdb-cluster-public` service.\n\n2. **Metrics endpoint is reachable** inside the cluster — a direct `curl -sk https://crdb-cluster-public.../_status/vars` returns valid Prometheus-format metrics.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Created a `ServiceMonitor` (Prometheus Operator CRD) in the `cockroachdb` namespace — the namespace Prometheus is already configured to watch (`serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector: {matchNames: [cockroachdb]}`).\n- Configured it to scrape path `/_status/vars` on the `http` (8080) port with `scheme: https` and `insecureSkipVerify: true` (CockroachDB redirects HTTP→HTTPS with a self-signed cert).\n- Added `prometheus-scrape: \"true\"` label to `crdb-cluster-public` to distinguish it from the headless `crdb-cluster` service so we get exactly 3 targets (one per node, not 6)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":39445,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c44be910-2177-44c8-8141-84d51b2060dc","uuid":"8d9af204-047b-499e-b581-a8416e8e90d1","request_id":"req_011CccAk5uWkNeJNwfZ1p54u"}
